# Sūra XLIV.: Du<u>kh</u>ān, or Smoke (or Mist.)

### Section 2

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_030.gif)

30. Walaqad najjayn<u>a</u> banee isr<u>a</u>-eela mina
alAAa<u>tha</u>bi almuheen**i**

30\. We did deliver aforetime  
The Children of Israel  
From humiliating Punishment,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_031.gif)

31. Min firAAawna innahu k<u>a</u>na AA<u>a</u>liyan mina
almusrifeen**a**

31\. Inflicted by Pharaoh, for he  
Was arrogant (even) among  
Inordinate transgressors.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_032.gif)

32. Walaqadi ikhtarn<u>a</u>hum AAal<u>a</u> AAilmin AAal<u>a</u>
alAA<u>a</u>lameen**a**

32\. And We chose them aforetime  
Above the nations, knowingly,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_033.gif)

33. Wa<u>a</u>tayn<u>a</u>hum mina al-<u>a</u>y<u>a</u>ti m<u>a</u>
feehi bal<u>a</u>on mubeen**un**

33\. And granted them Signs  
In which there was  
A manifest trial.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_034.gif)

34. Inna h<u>a</u>ol<u>a</u>-i layaqooloon**a**

34\. As to these (Quraish),  
They say forsooth:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_035.gif)

35. In hiya ill<u>a</u> mawtatun<u>a</u> al-ool<u>a</u> wam<u>a</u>
na<u>h</u>nu bimunshareen**a**

35\. "There is nothing beyond  
Our first death,  
And we shall not  
Be raised again.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_036.gif)

36. Fa/too bi-<u>a</u>b<u>a</u>-in<u>a</u> in kuntum
<u>sa</u>diqeen**a**

36\. "Then bring (back)  
Our forefathers, if what  
Ye say is true!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_037.gif)

37. Ahum khayrun am qawmu tubbaAAin wa**a**lla<u>th</u>eena min qablihim
ahlakn<u>a</u>hum innahum k<u>a</u>noo mujrimeen**a**

37\. What! are they better  
Than the people of Tubba‘  
And those who were  
Before them? We destroyed  
Them because they were  
Guilty of sin.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_038.gif)

38. Wam<u>a</u> khalaqn<u>a</u> a**l**ssam<u>a</u>w<u>a</u>ti
wa**a**l-ar<u>d</u>a wam<u>a</u> baynahum<u>a</u> l<u>a</u>AAibeen**a**

38\. We created not  
The heavens, the earth,  
And all between them,  
Merely in (idle) sport:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_039.gif)

39. M<u>a</u> khalaqn<u>a</u>hum<u>a</u> ill<u>a</u>
bi**a**l<u>h</u>aqqi wal<u>a</u>kinna aktharahum l<u>a</u>
yaAAlamoon**a**

39\. We created them not  
Except for just ends:  
But most of them  
Do not understand.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_040.gif)

40. Inna yawma alfa<u>s</u>li meeq<u>a</u>tuhum ajmaAAeen**a**

40\. Verily the Day of  
Sorting Out is the time  
Appointed for all of them,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_041.gif)

41. Yawma l<u>a</u> yughnee mawlan AAan mawlan shay-an wal<u>a</u> hum
yun<u>s</u>aroon**a**

41\. The Day when no protector  
Can avail his client  
In aught, and no help  
Can they receive,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/044/044_042.gif)

42. Ill<u>a</u> man ra<u>h</u>ima All<u>a</u>hu innahu huwa alAAazeezu
a**l**rra<u>h</u>eem**u**

42\. Except such as receive  
God's Mercy: for He is  
Exalted in Might, Most Merciful.

